<div </div
&nbsp;
The earthquake that hit&nbsp yesterday; the north-west of the country was clearly felt also &nbsp; in nearby Thailand, where several buildings were damaged and at least one, a skyscraper, collapsed in Bangkok causing the death of about ten people.
Chinese President Xi Jinping today sent a condolence message to the head of the Myanmar junta, Min Aung Hlaing. In the text, Xi "has expressed deep sadness" for the damage caused by the earthquake, we read in a statement of the Beijing Foreign Ministry. China has assured the president, is "willed to provide Myanmar with the necessary assistance to support people in the affected areas". Beijing has already sent in Myanmar a team of 82 rescuers, > responding to the appeal of the leader of the junta. Another team from Yunnan arrived in Yangon, Central Myanmar. The Chinese government will provide emergency humanitarian aid for 100 million yuan (12.7 million euros).
In any case, even in southern China the sisma has made itself felt: more than 800 houses have been damaged in the municipality of Ruili, > in the province&nbsp;Yunnan, has announced the official Xinhua press agency. And almost three thousand people affected in the city located about 300 kilometers from the epicentre of the sisma, two reported slight injuries. Local administrations have mobilized several rescue teams, monitoring geological risks, inspection of water basins, repair of electrical installations and road operations. The supply of water and electricity as well as transport and telecommunications are back to normal.
