<h2>Edifici evacuati a Bangkok</h2>
Another earthquake shock, magnitude of 5.5 - was recorded on yesterday's day in Bangkok. Residents of the Thai capital are on the road, preying to fear, while the buildings trembled. All offices and shops were evacuated by the authorities. &nbsp;
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
"I heard it and I was sleeping in the house, I ran as quickly as possible in pajamas outside the building", said Duangjai, a resident of the popular tourist town of Chiang Mai, after the shocks were felt throughout northern, central and then south Thailand.
