The Ministry of Foreign Affairs of South Korea stated that it will send US$2 million into humanitarian aid "to support rescue and rescue efforts", adding that it could send further aid if the situation had to worsen. The Iranian Ministry of Foreign Affairs sent Tehran's condolences to the people and governments of Myanmar and Thailand and said he was ready to contribute to humanitarian efforts
&nbsp;
