Thanks to the recent WHO experience with earthquakes in Turkey and Syria, "we know very well what to send first", said Harris. The organization already has a special cell working in Myanmar, devastated by fighting between the rebel forces and the army. "We are ready to go, but now we need to know exactly where, what and why. This is the ground information that is really fundamental right now."
